  "prompt": "How much would a wedding at a 5 star hotel in Mumbai for 400 people cost? Websites shows per-plate cost, does this include venue rental charges?",
  "response": "The cost of a wedding at a 5-star hotel in Mumbai can vary widely depending on several factors, including the hotel's prestige, location, the time of year, and the specific services included. \n\n1. **Per-Plate Cost**: This typically refers to the catering charges for food and beverages, and it usually does not include venue rental charges, decor, or additional services. Per-plate rates can range from \u20b92,000 to \u20b95,000 or even more, depending on the hotel's offerings.\n\n2. **Venue Rental Charges**: These are often separate from the per-plate cost. Some hotels may offer package deals that include venue rental, while others may charge separately. Venue rental can cost anywhere from \u20b950,000 to several lakhs, depending on the size of the space and the hotel's policies.\n\n3. **Additional Costs**: \n   - **Decor**: This can vary significantly based on your preferences and the complexity of the setup.\n   - **Photography & Videography**: This is often an additional expense.\n   - **Entertainment**: Live music, DJs, and other entertainment options will add to the budget.\n   - **Licensing or Permits**: Depending on the venue, there may be additional fees.\n   - **Additional Services**: This can include bridal services, planning assistance, and so on.\n\nGiven these factors, a rough estimate for a wedding with 400 guests at a 5-star hotel in Mumbai could range from \u20b920 lakhs to \u20b91 crore or more, depending on your specific choices and requirements. It's advisable to get quotes from specific hotels and clarify what is included in their packages to get a more accurate budget.",
